time required: 20 minutes
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #large pot{} of @water{} with @salt{} to a boil.
Once boiling, add @linguine{6%ounce} and cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente,
~{10-12%minutes}. Carefully scoop out and reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then
drain.

Meanwhile, halve @zucchini{1}(halved lengthwise and sliced into ¼-inch-thick
half-moons). Thinly slice half the @chili pepper{1}(sliced; if you like it spicy,
feel free to use all). Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce}, then pat dry with a #paper towel{},
removing as much moisture as you can.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{5%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high
heat. Add zucchini and chili and cook, tossing occasionally, until zucchini is
lightly browned, about ~{2%minutes}.

Push zucchini to one side of pan and add another large drizzle of olive oil to
center. Add shrimp and cook, tossing occasionally, until pink and just cooked
through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add linguine, @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon}, half the
@parmesan cheese{¼%cup}, and ¼ cup pasta cooking water to pan. Season with plenty
of salt and @pepper{}. Toss until combined and coated in a loose sauce.

> TIP: Add remaining ¼ cup pasta cooking water, as needed, if mixture seems dry.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan and a drizzle of
olive oil.

> TIP: Garnish with additional chili (to taste) for extra heat.